    <sec id="Sec17">
      <title>scRNA-seq data analysis</title>
      <p id="Par47">We applied the DE analysis methods that consider subject effect to macrophage and fibroblast separately from the three real datasets. Method performance was assessed based on the consistency of the identified DE genes between datasets. Genes with a <italic>p</italic> valueâ&lt;â0.01 were considered to be differentially expressed. The cell-level effect coefficient [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR20">20</xref>] was used to demonstrate subject variation. To calculate the effect coefficient for each cell, we calculated dot products of log-normalized expression and the estimated group effects across the DE genes identified by iDESC and then scaled to a maximum absolute value of 1. To compare the consistency of DE genes between datasets, Fisherâs exact test was used to assess the significance of overlap and Jaccard index was calculated to measure the similarity between the two DE gene lists. For the overlapping DE genes between the two chosen datasets identified by each method in each cell type, we validated them using a list of 83 genes that are related to IPF in the Harmonizome database (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://maayanlab.cloud/Harmonizome/">https://maayanlab.cloud/Harmonizome/</ext-link>).Â The proportion of validated genes was calculated as the percentage of 83 genes that were the between-dataset overlapping DE genes.</p>
    </sec>
